	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=64677"><span id="Sage">xaanru</span></a><br /><b><span id="Sage">Sage</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">3450 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Default [2.10]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>The screaming mace isn't that good a weapon, even for a low-level non-twink. My first character used an even worse weapon, a velium morningstar, until about level 12, when I ran across my first Sarnak enforcer. This sucker is a 7dmg, 28 delay 1hb weapon, that only weighs 2 stone. True, it doesn't have the proc, but will still outdamage the screaming mace, even with the proc. They usually sell for about 25-40pp, so one hq bear skin and you've got one. If I had known about them sooner, I would have had one by level 5, especially since some jerk conned me into paying 50pp for the velium morningstar.<br/><br/>The prayer shawl, on the other hand, is a nice +3wis shoulder item, with the same ac as leather. Braided ivy cords are better, but fairly expensive, and hard to get for low level. My druid is lvl 10, and I beleive this quest will be the next item on his agenda.</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br /><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=927520 target=akztarg>Xaanru's stuff</a></td></tr>
